76
00:04:35,023 --> 00:04:40,147
In a traditional narrative, in books, in TV, in movies,

77
00:04:40,987 --> 00:04:44,450
a hero is often called to action, and through a series of events,

78
00:04:45,010 --> 00:04:49,474
they strive to overcome challenges in order to achieve a goal.

79
00:04:50,894 --> 00:04:57,276
And why is this? And audiences really enjoy these narratives, that you see this form,

80
00:04:58,236 --> 00:05:03,118
this sort of basic structure, in all sorts of narratives that audiences relate to.

81
00:05:04,118 --> 00:05:08,319
And why? Because they can step inside the shoes of at least one of these characters.

82
00:05:08,359 --> 00:05:15,481
They can empathize. And suddenly, they feel like they get the rush of, that they're overcoming a challenge,

83
00:05:15,561 --> 00:05:17,942
and they get the excitement of trying to achieve a goal.

84
00:05:19,342 --> 00:05:23,864
In a game narrative, it's a little bit like this traditional narrative structure,

85
00:05:24,405 --> 00:05:25,845
but it's a little bit different as well.

86
00:05:26,205 --> 00:05:30,447
In a game narrative, the player is performing the actions that influence events,

87
00:05:31,248 --> 00:05:36,610
and they're learning to master a system and rules that you put in front of them to achieve their goal.

88
00:05:37,391 --> 00:05:42,033
So, basically a game narrative structure, the player is the hero.

89
00:05:43,413 --> 00:05:45,995
And I just want to emphasize that because that's really important.

90
00:05:46,775 --> 00:05:48,897
The player is the hero.

91
00:05:50,439 --> 00:05:57,307
So, a lot of games take a lot of time to try to create an association between an avatar and the player.

92
00:05:57,507 --> 00:06:00,490
They try to make you feel like you are this collection of pixels.

93
00:06:00,510 --> 00:06:02,873
You're Mario, you're Batman, you're Q-Bert.

94
00:06:04,482 --> 00:06:11,107
But the avatar is not the hero. The avatar's story is completely directed by an outside force.

95
00:06:11,387 --> 00:06:19,633
It's the player that is chasing a goal that's in their head, overcoming challenges that feel real to them.

96
00:06:20,253 --> 00:06:25,317
It's the player that's taking the action. They are the hero of the game narrative.

