196
00:11:30,839 --> 00:11:32,000
That's probably you.

197
00:11:33,422 --> 00:11:36,246
And you can have someone else work on this with you too,

198
00:11:36,266 --> 00:11:40,091
but I'd say one or at most two people should be involved in the actual construction of a prototype.

199
00:11:40,842 --> 00:11:43,743
If you have a lot of collaborators, that doesn't mean that you can't brainstorm

200
00:11:44,203 --> 00:11:45,724
and come up with ideas beforehand.

201
00:11:46,224 --> 00:11:47,685
But the people that are doing the building,

202
00:11:48,265 --> 00:11:50,826
you want to keep that small because you have such a short time frame

203
00:11:50,886 --> 00:11:52,647
and want ideas to be really pure and clean.

204
00:11:54,087 --> 00:11:55,748
And you want some simple supplies.

205
00:11:57,629 --> 00:11:59,850
So, a couple things that are important here.

206
00:11:59,870 --> 00:12:02,811
A little dry erase board can be very useful.

207
00:12:04,252 --> 00:12:06,574
playing cards, a couple pieces from old board games,

208
00:12:06,975 --> 00:12:09,677
post-it notes are great because they're sticky but not too sticky,

209
00:12:09,697 --> 00:12:10,498
you can move them around.

210
00:12:11,099 --> 00:12:12,220
But basically most of this stuff,

211
00:12:12,881 --> 00:12:14,623
you're going to either have around

212
00:12:14,643 --> 00:12:16,224
or you're going to be able to get when you need it.

213
00:12:17,998 --> 00:12:19,859
you also based on your idea you need

214
00:12:20,380 --> 00:12:21,620
some narrative reference points

215
00:12:22,201 --> 00:12:23,661
at least one game that has

216
00:12:24,141 --> 00:12:25,402
real similarities to your idea

